-- Activist investor Bramson ups stake in Electra Private Equity
-- 
-- Mon Mar 17, 2014 08:18AM EDT
-- None



LONDON, March 17 (Reuters) - Activist investor Edward Bramson has raised his stake in one of Britain's oldest private equity firms, Electra Private Equity <ELTA.L>, months after banking hefty profits on the sale of a stake in peer 3i <III.L>.

Sherborne Investors, the investment vehicle run by the media-shy entrepreneur, now has an 18.39 percent stake in the company, Electra Private Equity said in a statement, up from 13.7 percent on Feb. 28, when Sherborne announced its interest.